Fix 3 — Fix the seve_theme_color state desync bug (Critical)
Prompt for DeepSeek:
In src/layouts/EditorLayout.tsx, around line 531, there is this line:
  const themeColor = activeResume?.themeColor || localStorage.getItem('seve_theme_color') || '#b91c1c'

And the setter also writes to localStorage:
  localStorage.setItem('seve_theme_color', color)

This is a bug: themeColor has two sources of truth. Remove the localStorage fallback entirely. The themeColor should only come from the active resume profile in context (activeResume?.themeColor ?? '#b91c1c'). Also remove the localStorage.setItem('seve_theme_color', color) line from the setter — the theme color is already persisted inside the main seve_state AppState via updateActiveResume.

